	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f105658578754048>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=6990&mid=105658578754048>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=6990&mid=105658578754048>Usefull WPN</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=6990&mid=105658578754048#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jun 25th 8:45 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=119675><span id=Guru>kirbyramz</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>120 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Ok, where this wpn comes into play is when you are farming for trades skills supplies.&nbsp;&nbsp;Example is Acrylia or Velium Bricks.  Even at 58 I dont like to take on 10 RyGorrs at once without rooting and dotting them all as I hunt down more in CCaverns.  I put up my best buff and regen spells along with coat and shield of blades and then try to smack up a small train of 4-7 to follow me to a root area where I can root em in a row and use sleeves to dot em down.  Having this wpn allows you to avoid the multiple spell interruptions while trying to cast.  Plus you want em rooted so they wont run away and wont just turn from a snare at 20%.  You dont want to have to melee em down, you want them to die on your pin cushion.  Hitting them for near 40pts per thorn per swipe is much faster way to take down 7-10 of them than trying to get off the aoe quake spell or whatever.</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=899422" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=899422</a><br>EClapton<br>66th Human Bard<br>Leader, Holy Might Guild<br>Seventh Hammer</td></tr>
