	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=82901><span id=Scholar>JackOfSpeed</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>69 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.24]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Neat item for druids. This will undoubtedly be a highly sought item by the class and will probably only be weilded by the most elite - at least for now. I'd love to see how well this item works. In my experience with EQ, theres a pretty good chance that the proc will get resisted about 50% of the time if you're using it on yellow, blue or even mobs. It's a nice finishing item for kiting, except that when you've got a nearly dead mob snared he doesn't hit back, but if this proc sticks he'll turn around and start smacking you because of the root effect.<br>A nice thing about using it in melee is that even if it procs, the root will not overwrite any snares on the poor bastage, so he's in double trouble. And if you're grouped, a proc from this thing may save the day for a chanty, a cleric or an overzealous nuker. Its always nice to have a beefy mob stay put so your true melee types can lay the smack down, and your fragile chantys and clerics don't get atomic-wedgied by a pissed off mob. <br>I'd say that most druids agree that the spell this blade casts costs too much mana and doesn't stick enough to merit using up a memory slot most of the time. It has limited applications, but when you're in a group this could be a pretty useful item from time to time. And hell, you haven't meleed since level 15 - this scimmy might get you to wade right back into it.<br>I'm still waiting for them to come out with a druid only 1hs called "Blade of Grass".</p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>"Its probably better to be fat than ugly. You can always get less fat, but there ain't no cure for ugly... except maybe beer."</td></tr>
